Today! Join us at 12pm Central time for OPA’s free "Lunch and Learn", where we will be hosting Julie Snyder of @workshopsinfrance Julie will be talking all about international workshops and how to get the most from them, and so much more! 

This will be a lively and informative discussion - plus we’ll be making a very exciting announcement about my next international workshop (with my friend and amazing painter @janehuntart) in the south of France! Hope to see you there!

I've been devastated by the news from Maui and it's been impossible to comprehend the destruction. Having been fortunate to participate in the Maui Plein Air Invitational for many years, I feel a connection to this beautiful, sacred place. As plein air painters know, you personally connect to the sites, smells and sounds of a location when you are able to immerse yourself in your surroundings while painting from life. 

It's hard to believe that my painting, "Along Front Street", painted on Front Street looking toward the Pioneer Hotel, is now a record of buildings that are no longer standing.

@artistsforlahaina is organizing an auction to raise relief funds for our friends in Maui, please check them out on Facebook and Instagram
.
.
.
#maui #supportmaui #lahaina #artistsforlahaina

@micheleusibelliart is a versatile artist with a unique and instantly recognizable style. Her work is characterized by its loose brushstrokes, bold colors, and strong sense of light and shadow. Michele is drawn to many different painting genres, including still life, landscape, cityscapes, and figurative work.

However, it’s her individual style and paint application that creates a constant theme throughout her body of work!

Discover more about her new video, Painting with Gouache, at PaintTube.tv or the link in our bio.
